<p class="text-size-1">
	Phu Kradueng is a national park in Loei, Thailand set on top of a flat mountain summit plateau
	which covers 60km² and has a max elevation of 1,316 meters high.
</p>

<p>
	When my wife and I set of, we knew nothing about the mountain. All we had to go on was an
	over Instagramed photo of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phu_Kradueng_National_Park#/media/File:Lom_Sak_Cliff_(I).jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lom sak cliff</a>.
</p>

<p>
	The night before we set off, we stayed at a nearby goat farm that put its converted barn on
	AirBNB, it was an ideal place to rest before the hike.
</p>

