<p>
	We left the farm at about 8am, we thought it’d be a fairly leisurely hike, so this would give us
	plenty of time before the sun was at its hottest. We were wrong. By the time we started the ascent
	it was already 9:00AM and it was soon pushing a humid 30°C.
</p>

<p>
	We were pleased to reach the first major checkpoint by about 11:00AM, greeted by vendors selling
	food and much needed ice drinks as well as a stunning view. I thought to myself that it looked
	like we were almost there!
</p>

