<p>
	I got talking to a couple who had been up the mountain before, they told me that we were only
	about a quarter of the way up and that the hardest part was yet to come. They laughed at the
	shocked expression on my face, I had definitely underestimated this mountain.
</p>

<p>
	We pushed on the winding rocky steep path through the jungle, the heat was relentless but frequent
	checkpoints with vendors selling drinks and snacks kept us going throughout the day.
</p>

